.TH MONSTAR 1 "2026-07-13" "monstar" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
monstar \- a small Wayland terminal emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B monstar
.RI [ options ]
.br
.B monstar
.RI [ options ]
.B \-e
.I command
.RI [ argument ...]
.br
.B monstar
.RI [ options ]
.B \-\-
.I command...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B monstar
is a Wayland terminal emulator written in Zig and built on Ghostty's terminal
core.
With no command-line command or configured command, it starts the program named
by
.BR SHELL ,
falling back to
.BR /bin/sh .
.PP
Commands after
.B \-e
are executed directly.
Commands after
.B \-\-
are joined with spaces and passed to
.BR /bin/sh " " \-c .
Bare command names without either marker are rejected.
.SH OPTIONS
Long options that take a value accept either
.B "--option value"
or
.BR "--option=value" .
.TP
.BR \-h , " " \-\-help
Print usage information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print the version identifier and exit.
.TP
.BI \-\-title " title"
Set the initial window title.
The default is
.BR monstar .
.TP
.BI \-\-app-id " app-id"
Override the
.B app-id
configuration value for this invocation.
.TP
.BI \-\-working-directory " directory"
Start the child in
.IR directory .
The directory must exist and be accessible.
.TP
.B \-\-hold
Keep the window open after the child exits.
.TP
.BI \-\-window-size-chars " columns" x rows
Set the initial terminal grid size in cells.
Both dimensions must be positive and no greater than 65535.
.TP
.BI \-\-window-size-pixels " width" x height
Set the initial window size in physical pixels.
Both dimensions must be positive.
.TP
.BI \-\-font " family"
Override the
.B font-family
configuration value for this invocation.
.TP
.BI \-\-config " path"
Load
.I path
instead of the default configuration file.
A missing or unreadable file results in default configuration values.
.TP
.BI \-o " key=value"
Override a configuration value after loading the configuration file.
This option may be repeated and also accepts the compact form
.BR \-okey=value .
Unknown keys and invalid values make the command line invalid.
See
.BR monstar (5)
for available keys.
.TP
.BI \-e " command" " [argument ...]"
Execute the command directly without a shell.
All remaining arguments belong to the command.
.TP
.BI \-\- " command..."
Join the remaining words with spaces and run the result through
.BR /bin/sh " " \-c .
Shell quoting must therefore be supplied as part of those arguments.
.SH COMMAND SELECTION
The command-line forms take precedence over the
.B command
configuration setting.
If neither is present,
.B monstar
uses
.B SHELL
and then
.B /bin/sh
as fallbacks.
.PP
The child environment is inherited except that
.B TERM
is set to
.BR xterm-ghostty .
.SH CONFIGURATION
The default configuration file is
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/config
or, when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset,
.IR $HOME/.config/monstar/config .
See
.BR monstar (5)
for syntax and all settings.
.PP
Press
.B Ctrl+Shift+,
or send
.B SIGUSR1
to reload the configuration.
Command-line
.B \-o
overrides are reapplied on every reload.
Most visual and interaction settings update the running window;
process-creation settings apply only when a child or window is created.
.SH KEYBOARD SHORTCUTS
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+C
Copy the current selection to the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+G
Pipe the last OSC 133-delimited command output to the configured
.BR pipe-command-output .
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+N
Open a new Monstar window in the current terminal directory.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+V
Paste from the clipboard.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+X
Jump to the next OSC 133 prompt.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+Z
Jump to the previous OSC 133 prompt.
.TP
.B Ctrl+Shift+,
Reload the configuration.
.TP
.BR Ctrl++ " or " Ctrl+=
Increase the font size for this window.
.TP
.B Ctrl+-
Decrease the font size for this window.
.TP
.B Ctrl+0
Reset the runtime font-size override.
.SH POINTER INPUT
Drag with the left button to select text.
Hold
.B Ctrl
while dragging for a rectangular selection.
Middle-click pastes the primary selection.
.PP
When an application enables terminal mouse reporting, pointer input is sent to
the application.
Holding
.B Shift
bypasses application mouse reporting for terminal-side selection.
.PP
Hold
.B Ctrl
and left-click an OSC 8 hyperlink or detected URI to open it.
Use
.B Ctrl+Shift
when the application captures mouse input.
.PP
Wheel input is sent as mouse reports when requested by the application.
On the alternate screen without mouse reporting it is translated to arrow
keys; otherwise it scrolls the terminal scrollback.
.SH SIGNALS
.TP
.B SIGUSR1
Reload the configuration file and reapply command-line overrides.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Base directory for the configuration file and user themes.
.TP
.B HOME
Used for configuration and user-theme paths when
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
is unset.
.TP
.B SHELL
Default child command when no command is otherwise configured.
.TP
.B MONSTAR_RESOURCES_DIR
Override the resource directory used to find installed themes.
.TP
.B TERM
The inherited value is replaced with
.B xterm-ghostty
for the child.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/config
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/monstar/config
Fallback configuration file.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/monstar/themes/
User theme directory.
.TP
.I $HOME/.config/monstar/themes/
Fallback user theme directory.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Command-line syntax and option-value errors exit with status 2.
Startup or runtime failures exit nonzero.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR monstar (5),
.BR sh (1)
.SH BUGS
Report bugs at
.IR https://github.com/rockorager/monstar/issues .
